column2:
Three runs end to carve the way;
Turn your world completely grey.
Crystal balls will tell you how;
Enlightenment begins now.

Careful, do not break the chain;
Keep in mind how you are slain.
Three steps, three eyes, all will see;
Death will prove yourself to me.

First, a crystal-tethered ghost;
Let it make yourself its host.
Find it on the seventh floor;
Die to it. Open the door.

Next, a quite uncommon death;
Toxic sludge must stop your breath.
Stain yourself and let it burn;
Die to it. Then you will learn.

Third, the final boss enhanced;
Fruit is harmless at a glance.
Bring to Three-eyes' lair a gourd;
Die to it. Claim your reward.

Prove yourself on this death quest;
Succeed and you will be blessed.
Don't restart, but do delay;
Patience paves your own pathway.
